{
  "texts": [
    "KBQA is the task of answering natural language questions based on facts in a knowledge base.",
    "NSQA generates AMR for a given question, and then uses a novel graph transformation technique to generate candidate logical queries aligned with a knowledge base.",
    "These logical queries are then Logical Neural Network to produce the final answer.",
    "Another example is the Question Decomposition method based on AMR (QDAMR) [24], introduced for multi-hop question answering.",
    "QDAMR utilizes AMR to achieve interpretable reasoning by decomposing complex, multi-hop questions into simpler sub-questions.This is achieved by segmenting the AMR graph based on reasoning types."
  ]
}